An unclosed literal !`oops leaves the rest of the line alone.

This paragraph must stay ordinary prose, not literal content.

An unclosed math $`oops must not leak either.

This paragraph must stay ordinary prose, not math content.

Closed forms still scope: !`/kaet/` and $`E = mc^2` and $$`\int_0^1 x`.

Multi-backtick fences still work: !``a`b`` and $``a`b``.

Attributes still attach: !`x`{.ipa} and $`y`{.big}.

An escaped bang \!`x` is an ordinary code span.
